00:00:08.313 --> 00:00:11.247 align:middle line:90%
[THEME MUSIC]

00:00:11.247 --> 00:00:19.100 align:middle line:90%


00:00:19.100 --> 00:00:21.860 align:middle line:10%
>> REGINA MEREDITH: There's been
one consistent message about how

00:00:21.860 --> 00:00:23.960 align:middle line:10%
to contend with these
chaotic and, for some,

00:00:23.960 --> 00:00:27.300 align:middle line:10%
even frightening times,
to return to nature.

00:00:27.300 --> 00:00:29.480 align:middle line:84%
We have a very special
guest with us today

00:00:29.480 --> 00:00:33.110 align:middle line:84%
whose lineage is to live in
harmony with Mother Earth, which

00:00:33.110 --> 00:00:34.950 align:middle line:84%
we all need to
start considering.

00:00:34.950 --> 00:00:37.500 align:middle line:84%
Chase Iron Eyes is a
member of the Sioux tribe.

00:00:37.500 --> 00:00:39.110 align:middle line:84%
He's here to tell
us all about how

00:00:39.110 --> 00:00:42.030 align:middle line:84%
nature will heal our
ailing people and cultures

00:00:42.030 --> 00:00:43.290 align:middle line:90%
and so much more.

00:00:43.290 --> 00:00:45.538 align:middle line:84%
Chase, it's wonderful to
be here with you today.

00:00:45.538 --> 00:00:47.580 align:middle line:84%
>> CHASE IRON EYES: Man,
thank you for having me.

00:00:47.580 --> 00:00:49.020 align:middle line:84%
>> REGINA: I get
your newsletter,

00:00:49.020 --> 00:00:51.000 align:middle line:90%
so I follow what you're doing.

00:00:51.000 --> 00:00:52.920 align:middle line:84%
A lot of it having to
do with Dakota pipeline.

00:00:52.920 --> 00:00:54.420 align:middle line:84%
We're going to get
into all of that.

00:00:54.420 --> 00:00:58.020 align:middle line:84%
But first, many people
don't know your culture.

00:00:58.020 --> 00:01:00.940 align:middle line:84%
I mean, they've seen movies,
maybe read a book or two.

00:01:00.940 --> 00:01:03.450 align:middle line:84%
But to really
understand your culture

00:01:03.450 --> 00:01:06.570 align:middle line:84%
and the modern
implications of what

00:01:06.570 --> 00:01:08.700 align:middle line:84%
happened, even starting
with your mother

00:01:08.700 --> 00:01:11.530 align:middle line:90%
when things started going awry.

00:01:11.530 --> 00:01:15.810 align:middle line:84%
So shall we begin talking
about your mother?

00:01:15.810 --> 00:01:19.290 align:middle line:84%
And you're from Standing Rock
Reservation, which many people

00:01:19.290 --> 00:01:21.880 align:middle line:84%
have heard of the Standing Rock
Reservation in North Dakota.

00:01:21.880 --> 00:01:22.680 align:middle line:90%
So--

00:01:22.680 --> 00:01:23.100 align:middle line:90%
>> IRON EYES: Yes.

00:01:23.100 --> 00:01:23.920 align:middle line:90%
>> REGINA: Yes.

00:01:23.920 --> 00:01:28.480 align:middle line:10%
>> IRON EYES: I was born in the
Black Hills of South Dakota,

00:01:28.480 --> 00:01:29.980 align:middle line:10%
what is now called South Dakota.

00:01:29.980 --> 00:01:40.260 align:middle line:10%
And [SPEAKING LAKOTA] is what we
call the Black Hills, the heart

00:01:40.260 --> 00:01:43.020 align:middle line:10%
of everything that is.

00:01:43.020 --> 00:01:48.130 align:middle line:84%
And my mother, she
had a long story,

00:01:48.130 --> 00:01:51.660 align:middle line:90%
a long, controverted history.

00:01:51.660 --> 00:01:57.120 align:middle line:84%
She was taken to a boarding
school in South Dakota,

00:01:57.120 --> 00:01:58.440 align:middle line:90%
along with my uncle.

00:01:58.440 --> 00:02:05.870 align:middle line:84%
And it was-- since the inception
of the reservation era,

00:02:05.870 --> 00:02:09.285 align:middle line:84%
Native people have
been through a lot.

00:02:09.285 --> 00:02:14.760 align:middle line:84%
We're still navigating an
ongoing colonial experience.

00:02:14.760 --> 00:02:18.410 align:middle line:90%
For us, it's not post-colonial.

00:02:18.410 --> 00:02:19.500 align:middle line:90%
>> REGINA: No, not at all.

00:02:19.500 --> 00:02:19.555 align:middle line:90%
You're--

00:02:19.555 --> 00:02:19.610 align:middle line:90%
>> IRON EYES: Not at all.

00:02:19.610 --> 00:02:20.780 align:middle line:90%
>> REGINA: --living in it.

00:02:20.780 --> 00:02:23.180 align:middle line:84%
>> IRON EYES: And you saw
that at Standing Rock,

00:02:23.180 --> 00:02:25.400 align:middle line:90%
at the pipeline ordeal.

00:02:25.400 --> 00:02:29.160 align:middle line:90%
And so we lost a lot.

00:02:29.160 --> 00:02:29.960 align:middle line:90%
There's a lot of--

00:02:29.960 --> 00:02:32.043 align:middle line:84%
>> REGINA: Can you go back
a little bit and tell--

00:02:32.043 --> 00:02:35.600 align:middle line:84%
how was your mother living,
what was her life like, and then

00:02:35.600 --> 00:02:38.030 align:middle line:84%
the reservation
life, and then being

00:02:38.030 --> 00:02:41.060 align:middle line:84%
taken into this
boarding system where--

00:02:41.060 --> 00:02:46.400 align:middle line:84%
boarding school system where
tradition was encouraged

00:02:46.400 --> 00:02:47.317 align:middle line:90%
to be forgotten about.

00:02:47.317 --> 00:02:48.117 align:middle line:90%
>> IRON EYES: Yeah.

00:02:48.117 --> 00:02:49.760 align:middle line:84%
>> REGINA: [LAUGHS]
To say it politely.

00:02:49.760 --> 00:02:53.390 align:middle line:84%
>> IRON EYES: Before the United
States Army Corps of Engineers

00:02:53.390 --> 00:02:55.590 align:middle line:84%
flooded the Standing
Rock reservation,

00:02:55.590 --> 00:03:00.150 align:middle line:84%
they flooded seven different
reservations for hydropower

00:03:00.150 --> 00:03:01.800 align:middle line:90%
for its own reasons.

00:03:01.800 --> 00:03:03.850 align:middle line:90%
They did not get our consent.

00:03:03.850 --> 00:03:08.040 align:middle line:84%
And my mother was
living off and on

00:03:08.040 --> 00:03:11.310 align:middle line:84%
between her mother and
father's house, which

00:03:11.310 --> 00:03:13.590 align:middle line:84%
was a square house,
American style

00:03:13.590 --> 00:03:19.080 align:middle line:84%
house, and her grandmother,
who was a medicine woman, who

00:03:19.080 --> 00:03:23.880 align:middle line:84%
practiced her art
and her healing ways

00:03:23.880 --> 00:03:28.170 align:middle line:84%
on the riverbed,
which was a very--

00:03:28.170 --> 00:03:30.220 align:middle line:84%
the most fertile
ground that we had.

00:03:30.220 --> 00:03:33.130 align:middle line:84%
We could make an
economic life from there.

00:03:33.130 --> 00:03:36.640 align:middle line:84%
All of our foods, medicines,
all of the habitats,

00:03:36.640 --> 00:03:38.730 align:middle line:84%
the riparian
habitats, everything

00:03:38.730 --> 00:03:41.220 align:middle line:90%
that is good about heavily--

00:03:41.220 --> 00:03:42.370 align:middle line:90%
about the ecosystems.

00:03:42.370 --> 00:03:43.680 align:middle line:90%
They're heavily wooded.

00:03:43.680 --> 00:03:45.010 align:middle line:90%
We depended on that.

00:03:45.010 --> 00:03:49.900 align:middle line:84%
And my mom spent a lot of time
with her grandmother there.

00:03:49.900 --> 00:03:53.350 align:middle line:84%
And I never got a chance to
meet my mother's grandmother,

00:03:53.350 --> 00:03:57.420 align:middle line:84%
but I was pretty much raised
by four different grandmothers

00:03:57.420 --> 00:03:58.980 align:middle line:90%
in my lifetime.

00:03:58.980 --> 00:04:03.070 align:middle line:84%
And she had a very
good life there,

00:04:03.070 --> 00:04:06.810 align:middle line:84%
but she could never make
sense of the contrast of why

00:04:06.810 --> 00:04:13.290 align:middle line:84%
does my grandmother,
who I cherish very much

00:04:13.290 --> 00:04:15.840 align:middle line:84%
and who helps the
community, why is she living

00:04:15.840 --> 00:04:20.310 align:middle line:84%
in this one-room shack
with a dirt floor

00:04:20.310 --> 00:04:23.940 align:middle line:84%
in a wood stove in
relative discomforts

00:04:23.940 --> 00:04:28.230 align:middle line:84%
compared to what her dad, who
worked for the Bureau of Indian

00:04:28.230 --> 00:04:31.530 align:middle line:84%
Affairs, had a
nice house and was

00:04:31.530 --> 00:04:40.390 align:middle line:84%
upwardly mobile in the oncoming
new political economic reality.

00:04:40.390 --> 00:04:45.930 align:middle line:84%
My grandfather, who I'm talking
about, was born in 1900.

00:04:45.930 --> 00:04:47.710 align:middle line:84%
So when we think
of Native people,

00:04:47.710 --> 00:04:49.780 align:middle line:84%
sometimes we think
of ancient history.

00:04:49.780 --> 00:04:55.980 align:middle line:84%
But that's because of how we've
been typecast by Western media.

00:04:55.980 --> 00:04:57.520 align:middle line:84%
>> REGINA: This
is modern history.

00:04:57.520 --> 00:04:58.480 align:middle line:84%
>> IRON EYES: It's
modern history.

00:04:58.480 --> 00:05:00.700 align:middle line:84%
This is my grandfather
that we're talking about,

00:05:00.700 --> 00:05:04.380 align:middle line:84%
who's 10 years younger than
the state of South Dakota

00:05:04.380 --> 00:05:08.100 align:middle line:90%
or the state of North Dakota.

00:05:08.100 --> 00:05:14.220 align:middle line:84%
But think of those as the
spiritual buffalo economy days

00:05:14.220 --> 00:05:18.460 align:middle line:84%
that we had come from and
from the 1870s onward, say,

00:05:18.460 --> 00:05:21.940 align:middle line:84%
after the Battle of Little
Bighorn, Custer's Last Stand,

00:05:21.940 --> 00:05:26.290 align:middle line:84%
then we start learning
to speak English.

00:05:26.290 --> 00:05:29.950 align:middle line:84%
Not voluntarily at first,
but sometimes voluntarily.

00:05:29.950 --> 00:05:34.900 align:middle line:84%
But the United States, in
conjunction with the churches,

00:05:34.900 --> 00:05:38.790 align:middle line:84%
imposed this boarding
school or residential school

00:05:38.790 --> 00:05:42.190 align:middle line:84%
era, which that is a
euphemism for that era.

00:05:42.190 --> 00:05:44.560 align:middle line:84%
That is an era of
cultural genocide.

00:05:44.560 --> 00:05:48.348 align:middle line:90%
It's an era complete--

00:05:48.348 --> 00:05:53.250 align:middle line:84%
the erasure and the degradation
of our internal dignity

00:05:53.250 --> 00:05:56.510 align:middle line:84%
that we're born
with and that we can

00:05:56.510 --> 00:05:59.720 align:middle line:84%
avail ourselves with
in different aspects.

00:05:59.720 --> 00:06:02.520 align:middle line:84%
A lot of us learn the
English language first now.

00:06:02.520 --> 00:06:06.300 align:middle line:84%
But for my mom and
for my grandparents,

00:06:06.300 --> 00:06:07.320 align:middle line:90%
that wasn't the case.

00:06:07.320 --> 00:06:09.200 align:middle line:84%
And there's a lot of
people alive today--

00:06:09.200 --> 00:06:11.750 align:middle line:84%
and that number is
going down, but they

00:06:11.750 --> 00:06:16.280 align:middle line:84%
learn Lakota first,
Lakhótiya Wóglaka, which

00:06:16.280 --> 00:06:20.690 align:middle line:90%
is another software, another--

00:06:20.690 --> 00:06:21.930 align:middle line:90%
it's another software.

00:06:21.930 --> 00:06:24.740 align:middle line:84%
Think of it like a
technology through which

00:06:24.740 --> 00:06:30.890 align:middle line:84%
we can access different
elemental universal powers

00:06:30.890 --> 00:06:32.520 align:middle line:90%
and relationships.

00:06:32.520 --> 00:06:35.340 align:middle line:84%
And yes, you can also get there
through the English language,

00:06:35.340 --> 00:06:39.210 align:middle line:84%
but all of our rituals,
our ceremonies, our songs,

00:06:39.210 --> 00:06:43.580 align:middle line:84%
our knowledge systems, all of
those are also available to us

00:06:43.580 --> 00:06:46.220 align:middle line:84%
in our language, in
the Lakota language.

00:06:46.220 --> 00:06:51.450 align:middle line:84%
But she goes to boarding
school, and it's horror stories.

00:06:51.450 --> 00:06:56.030 align:middle line:84%
It's the stuff of
torture, humiliation.

00:06:56.030 --> 00:06:58.610 align:middle line:84%
You get caught speaking
your Native language,

00:06:58.610 --> 00:07:00.550 align:middle line:84%
you're going to
put-- you're going

00:07:00.550 --> 00:07:02.650 align:middle line:84%
to kneel in the
corner on a broomstick

00:07:02.650 --> 00:07:07.930 align:middle line:84%
until they determine that
you've suffered long enough.

00:07:07.930 --> 00:07:09.860 align:middle line:90%
We've gone through that.

00:07:09.860 --> 00:07:16.600 align:middle line:84%
That resulted in a loss of
identity, cultural identity,

00:07:16.600 --> 00:07:28.810 align:middle line:84%
pride, dignity, a working
metaphysics or a system

00:07:28.810 --> 00:07:34.450 align:middle line:84%
of knowing whatever
the self is, one self,

00:07:34.450 --> 00:07:40.030 align:middle line:84%
your personalized experience,
your personalized consciousness.

00:07:40.030 --> 00:07:45.520 align:middle line:84%
We were recreated through the
lens of the European imagination

00:07:45.520 --> 00:07:47.260 align:middle line:90%
in those places.

00:07:47.260 --> 00:07:48.220 align:middle line:90%
And I'm sitting here

00:07:48.220 --> 00:07:49.310 align:middle line:84%
>> REGINA: These
are not compatible.

00:07:49.310 --> 00:07:50.570 align:middle line:90%
>> IRON EYES: These are not--

00:07:50.570 --> 00:07:53.930 align:middle line:84%
we've had to make them
compatible, because most of us

00:07:53.930 --> 00:07:57.570 align:middle line:84%
don't speak our Lakota or
traditional Indigenous language.

00:07:57.570 --> 00:07:59.870 align:middle line:84%
There's more than
probably 300 languages

00:07:59.870 --> 00:08:02.960 align:middle line:84%
still in what is now
called the United States.

00:08:02.960 --> 00:08:08.130 align:middle line:90%
But the times have shifted.

00:08:08.130 --> 00:08:13.670 align:middle line:84%
It's no longer termination
of tribal nations

00:08:13.670 --> 00:08:18.860 align:middle line:84%
and a degradation of spiritual
and political degradation

00:08:18.860 --> 00:08:20.250 align:middle line:90%
of Indigenous peoples.

00:08:20.250 --> 00:08:24.810 align:middle line:84%
We're trying to turn that
around and say, hey, look at--

00:08:24.810 --> 00:08:28.010 align:middle line:84%
we've all been
through some trauma.

00:08:28.010 --> 00:08:34.820 align:middle line:84%
We've all been separated from
a natural, mystic, spiritual

00:08:34.820 --> 00:08:37.140 align:middle line:90%
relationship with the universe.

00:08:37.140 --> 00:08:39.860 align:middle line:84%
We've all suffered that,
no matter what color

00:08:39.860 --> 00:08:43.039 align:middle line:90%
our skin is or what our--

00:08:43.039 --> 00:08:44.790 align:middle line:90%
>> REGINA: No, that is true.

00:08:44.790 --> 00:08:46.712 align:middle line:84%
And in that sense, that
extends to everyone.

00:08:46.712 --> 00:08:48.170 align:middle line:84%
And we've made
choices that-- where

00:08:48.170 --> 00:08:50.420 align:middle line:84%
we've done it to
ourselves, and it's also

00:08:50.420 --> 00:08:52.890 align:middle line:84%
been perpetuated upon
humanity by others

00:08:52.890 --> 00:08:56.018 align:middle line:90%
as well, as we well know.

00:08:56.018 --> 00:08:58.060 align:middle line:84%
I want to go back to your
language, for a moment.

00:08:58.060 --> 00:09:01.480 align:middle line:84%
So if you set a simple
sentence like, I am a member--

00:09:01.480 --> 00:09:03.430 align:middle line:84%
would you say Sioux of
the Sioux tribe then?

00:09:03.430 --> 00:09:04.230 align:middle line:90%
I am a member--

00:09:04.230 --> 00:09:06.670 align:middle line:84%
>> IRON EYES: In the legal
documents, yes, Sioux Nation.

00:09:06.670 --> 00:09:09.453 align:middle line:84%
>> REGINA: So if you would
say, I am a member of the Sioux

00:09:09.453 --> 00:09:11.620 align:middle line:84%
Nation, what would that
sound like in your language?

00:09:11.620 --> 00:09:12.420 align:middle line:90%
I want to feel it.

00:09:12.420 --> 00:09:13.920 align:middle line:90%
>> IRON EYES: Yeah.

00:09:13.920 --> 00:09:18.055 align:middle line:84%
You would say,
[SPEAKING LAKOTA].

00:09:18.055 --> 00:09:29.130 align:middle line:90%


00:09:29.130 --> 00:09:33.270 align:middle line:84%
I belong to the
Lakota people or the--

00:09:33.270 --> 00:09:37.680 align:middle line:84%
Oceti Sakowin is--
we were called Sioux

00:09:37.680 --> 00:09:41.720 align:middle line:90%
because of a misinterpretation.

00:09:41.720 --> 00:09:42.520 align:middle line:90%
Yeah.

00:09:42.520 --> 00:09:43.900 align:middle line:84%
>> REGINA: So your
language itself--

00:09:43.900 --> 00:09:44.820 align:middle line:90%
thank you for that.

00:09:44.820 --> 00:09:47.400 align:middle line:84%
The language itself, I just
wanted to hear a little,

00:09:47.400 --> 00:09:48.310 align:middle line:90%
feel a little.

00:09:48.310 --> 00:09:51.470 align:middle line:84%
The language itself clearly
isn't Germanic or Latin-based.

00:09:51.470 --> 00:09:56.980 align:middle line:84%
So your language, doing
the historical study

00:09:56.980 --> 00:09:59.020 align:middle line:90%
of the roots of language--

00:09:59.020 --> 00:09:59.890 align:middle line:90%
>> IRON EYES: Yes.

00:09:59.890 --> 00:10:01.765 align:middle line:84%
>> REGINA: --etymology
and some of the other.

00:10:01.765 --> 00:10:03.760 align:middle line:84%
I mean, I remember
reading some--

00:10:03.760 --> 00:10:08.500 align:middle line:84%
a couple of books I read had to
do with their Iroquois language

00:10:08.500 --> 00:10:10.810 align:middle line:84%
being at the root of
very, very ancient--

00:10:10.810 --> 00:10:13.940 align:middle line:84%
other places in the languages
in other parts of the world.

00:10:13.940 --> 00:10:15.370 align:middle line:90%
What is your language?

00:10:15.370 --> 00:10:16.870 align:middle line:84%
What do you know
about your language

00:10:16.870 --> 00:10:18.380 align:middle line:90%
and where it stemmed from?

00:10:18.380 --> 00:10:21.290 align:middle line:84%
Because it's a completely
different vibration.

00:10:21.290 --> 00:10:24.537 align:middle line:84%
And to have to cut that off
and go into a Germanic language

00:10:24.537 --> 00:10:27.550 align:middle line:84%
no less, thinking and
acting, just the language

00:10:27.550 --> 00:10:29.330 align:middle line:90%
itself would change everything.

00:10:29.330 --> 00:10:31.942 align:middle line:90%


00:10:31.942 --> 00:10:33.317 align:middle line:84%
>> IRON EYES:
Language, Lakolya--

00:10:33.317 --> 00:10:36.059 align:middle line:90%


00:10:36.059 --> 00:10:43.930 align:middle line:84%
the [LAKOTA], the [LAKOTA],
the teachings and the language

00:10:43.930 --> 00:10:47.738 align:middle line:90%
itself has otherworldly origins.

00:10:47.738 --> 00:10:49.280 align:middle line:84%
>> REGINA: That's
what I'm wondering.

00:10:49.280 --> 00:10:51.780 align:middle line:90%
Tell us about that.

00:10:51.780 --> 00:10:54.970 align:middle line:84%
>> IRON EYES: This is a long
story, and that's a long story.

00:10:54.970 --> 00:10:58.290 align:middle line:84%
But it involves the
creation of the universe

00:10:58.290 --> 00:11:05.070 align:middle line:84%
and the order of creation,
divine creation, sometimes

00:11:05.070 --> 00:11:08.730 align:middle line:84%
self-determined creation because
these gods or these spirits

00:11:08.730 --> 00:11:11.440 align:middle line:90%
have their own ambitions.

00:11:11.440 --> 00:11:13.680 align:middle line:90%
They have their own intentions.

00:11:13.680 --> 00:11:19.950 align:middle line:84%
And one particular-- he's not
a god or he's not really a he,

00:11:19.950 --> 00:11:21.790 align:middle line:90%
but it is not a god.

00:11:21.790 --> 00:11:28.110 align:middle line:84%
It is a servant, a role
player, this entity that

00:11:28.110 --> 00:11:33.630 align:middle line:84%
served the good spirits and even
the bad spirit, you might say.

00:11:33.630 --> 00:11:34.870 align:middle line:90%
They're all one.

00:11:34.870 --> 00:11:41.130 align:middle line:84%
And this particular entity
named Kssa served these gods.

00:11:41.130 --> 00:11:43.620 align:middle line:84%
And there was a time
when he would serve--

00:11:43.620 --> 00:11:47.130 align:middle line:84%
they would serve these
gods even white foods

00:11:47.130 --> 00:11:48.760 align:middle line:90%
underneath the earth.

00:11:48.760 --> 00:11:54.410 align:middle line:84%
And this particular person,
entity was ashamed of his form.

00:11:54.410 --> 00:11:57.310 align:middle line:84%
And so these negative
forces capitalized

00:11:57.310 --> 00:11:58.700 align:middle line:90%
on that, exploited that.

00:11:58.700 --> 00:12:00.200 align:middle line:90%
They like to cause mischief.

00:12:00.200 --> 00:12:04.180 align:middle line:84%
They like to embarrass
the good gods.

00:12:04.180 --> 00:12:06.910 align:middle line:84%
And they convinced
this particular entity

00:12:06.910 --> 00:12:11.620 align:middle line:84%
to go along with their
schemes, and this-- so he

00:12:11.620 --> 00:12:15.620 align:middle line:84%
